      <description>&lt;p&gt;Welcome to Wenjun Zhang&#39;s homepage! I am a senior year undergraduate student at Peking University. Atomic, molecular and optical (AMO) physics and quantum simulation capture my research interest. I did several research projects on ultracold quantum gases, optical lattices, matter-wave interferometer, and spin chains. Ultracold systems are clean and highly tunable, making them perfect platforms to perform quantum simulation and high-precision metrology. Now I am seeking for a Ph.D. position in physics or applied physics, and I hope to do some research on many-body physics or dynamics with ultracold systems.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
